   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Eight WHO SHALL BE IN THE LAKE OF FIRE Scripture: Rev 21:8 Those who will be in the lake of fire The fearful.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>These want to believe in Jesus but are afraid of others mocking.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The unbelieving.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>These would not receive the Lord Jesus as their Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The abominable.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>These do not believe in the true God, but rather worship idols.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>This is like an evil woman who loves another man besides her own husband and commits abominations.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The murderers.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Once a man worships idols, it is easy for him to commit sins and to hate and kill others.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The fornicators.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Today s newspapers, magazines, and movies are full of fornication.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The sorcerers.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>These include fortune-tellers, soothsayers, astrologists, etc. The idolaters.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Abomination and idolatry are nearly the same.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The difference is that abomination refers to the nature of idol worship, whereas idolatry refers to the act of idol worship.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The liars.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>All men are at least one of these eight kinds of people.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Whoever is none of these, please raise your hand.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>How to escape the lake of fire Repent.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>Believe in Jesus.</S>
   </TEXT>
